          <h1>Styleguide notes</h1>
          <hr />
          <h2>Product item in listing</h2>
          <hr />

          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>Displayed on the PLP it displays the product logo, name, unit amount, type, spotlight (if applicable), location, star rating and the voucher value.</p>

            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There are two layout modes: desktop and mobile. Larger screens lay out content horizontally. Smaller screens stack content vertically so it can wrap.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <h4>Media queries</h4>
            <p>We are using three breakpoints to handle the changes between desktop, tablet and mobile. Common styles are loaded for the component and then device specific styles are loaded in for each breakpoint into the appropriate stylesheet.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/listing-item.scss</p>
            <p>/large-components/listing-item.scss</p>
            <p>/small-components/listing-item.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Use of JavaScript</h3>
            <p>When clicking anywhere on the item row, the click event is triggered on the product title anchor.</p>
            <h4>Use of AJAX</h4>
            <p>N/A</p>
            <h4>Non-JS behaviour</h4>
            <p>Only the product title is clickable.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>Above are 5 variants of product type:</p>
            <p>There are two variants of the 'Money off' product showing how the spotlight text can be altered, a 'Fixed price' product, a 'Clubcard perk' product with no price and a price range product where a 'Fixed price' product can have different prices depending on the variant selected.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Responsive Images</h3>
            <p>The partner logo dimensions are 150 x 150. We recommend using the same image from the listing page as the graphic will be pre-cached and prevent an extra HTTP request. Because the image is resized to 50% this will prevent degradation on retina devices.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
            <p>Images should contain relevant alt text</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Character limit recommendations</h3>
            <p>Listing title: 40 characters per line</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
